<h1 id="toc1"><span>What this is</span></h1>
<p>This is an unofficial <a href="http://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/theme:black-highlighter-theme">Black Highlighter Theme</a> component that adds slick, animated BHL-style collapsible bars to your articles. It affects the existing <tt>[collapsible]</tt> element. Your articles will probably require only minor modification to be made compatible.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">CLICK&nbsp;ME!</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">CLICK&nbsp;ME!</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p><strong>Features:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Slick, excessive animations that will surely make at least a few people slam the upvote button</li>
<li>Compatible with mobile</li>
<li>Somewhat customizable (see below)</li>
<li>Literally does the addendum counting for you lmao</li>
<li>Standalone custom div decorations for those that don't care about the clicky smashy part</li>
<li>That arrow that faces right turns downward when it unfolds hOW COOL IS THAT!?</li>
<li>You know if you get enough upvotes, you might just finally be at peace with yourself. Come on, include the module. It's what you need.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Restrictions:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>It will affect <em>all</em> collapsibles. If you have some custom ones, you'll need to learn some CSS editing.</li>
<li>It looks very silly when you set <tt>hideLocation</tt>' to &quot;both&quot;</li>
<li>It does not magically add support for nested collapsibles. This is just CSS.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
