<h5 id="toc3"><span>Collapsible</span></h5>
<p><strong>Normal:</strong><br />
This component modifies the standard collapsible, so this is entirely the same. Heavily recommended that you make the 'show' and 'hide' fields the same.</p>
<p><em>Note:</em> The &quot;<tt>ADDENDUM XXXX.N</tt>&quot; is automatically added and incremented based on the number of previous collapsibles. It can be removed, see below.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">COOL&nbsp;THING</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">COOL&nbsp;THING</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<div class="code">
<pre>
<code>[[collapsible show=&quot;COOL THING&quot; hide=&quot;COOL THING&quot;]]
Stuff!
[[/collapsible]]</code>
</pre></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<br />
<strong>Always Unfolded:</strong><br />
To be clear, this is literally just an &quot;in-place&quot; decorative element. You aren't actually putting any of your article inside of this &quot;collapsible.&quot;
<p><em>Note:</em> The &quot;<tt>ADDENDUM XXXX.N</tt>&quot; counter is still incremented by these collapsibles.</p>
